Let the side length of the octagon be $a$. The length of $HI$ is $\sqrt{2a}$, so the area of $AHIJ$ is $2a \cdot \sqrt{2a} = 2a\sqrt{2}$.  Since $AH$ and $HJ$ divide $AHIJ$ into four congruent right triangles and $\triangle AFC$, the area of $\triangle    AFC = \frac82a\sqrt{2} - a = 2a\sqrt{2} - a$.

The area of $\odot ABCDEFGH$ is the area of the $\odot AHIJ$ minus the areas of four congruent right triangles. The area of $\odot AHIJ$ is $2a\sqrt{2}$, and the combined area of the four congruent right triangles is $a$, so the area of the $\odot ABCDEFGH$ is $2a\sqrt{2} - a = 1$ square unit. Solving the equation $2a\sqrt{2} - a = 1$ gives $a = \frac{1}{2\sqrt{2} - 1} = 2\sqrt{2} - 1$.

Rectangle $ABEF$ consists of a square of side length $a$ and two of the congruent right triangles with combined area equal to $a$. So, the area of $ABEF$ is $a + a = 2a = \boxed{2\sqrt{2} - 2}$.

