The octagon has independent symmetries about 2 perpendicular lines of reflection. Thus the two directions from each vertex to its opposite vertex partition the octagon into 4 congruent squares. Their diagonals partition them further into 8 congruent 45-45-90 triangles with hypotenuse 1.

The area of a 45-45-90 triangle is $\frac{1}{2}$ the square of the length of one of the legs.

