The sum of the angle measurements in triangle $ABC$ is $180^\circ$ since the angles of a triangle sum to $180^\circ$.  The angles of $ABC$ measure $30^\circ$, $75^\circ$, and $75^\circ$, so \begin{align*}
\angle AXB &= 180^\circ - \angle ABC \\
&= 180^\circ - 75^\circ \\
&= 105^\circ.
\end{align*} We also have $$\angle BXC = \angle BXA = \frac{1}{2}(180^\circ - \angle AXB) = \frac{1}{2}(180^\circ - 105^\circ) = 37.5^\circ.$$  Therefore, \begin{align*}
\angle AXC &= 180^\circ - \angle AXB - \angle BXC\\
&= 180^\circ - 105^\circ - 37.5^\circ \\
&= \boxed{37.5^\circ}.
\end{align*}

