We have that $[N_iO]=\sqrt{3}$, hence, $r=\sqrt{3}-1$ which is the radius of the big sphere. The radius of the 8th sphere is \[\overline{MO}-[MN_i]=[MQ]-[ON-Q]=[MT]-[ON]=[MS]-1=\frac{1}{3}\sqrt{3}-1.\] Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{\frac{1}{3}}$ when you subtract $\overline{MS}$ by $1$. [But how in the world did we know that $MT$ = $ON$? Well, because of the small sphere, MT and ON must coincide on the hexagon, so their lengths are equal. ---TDP]

